@startuml
' @id(SEQ-ARCH-TRACK)
' @ref(USE-TRACK-ARCH)
' @desc(SEQ-ARCH-TRACK, "How an agent tracks an architectural change: read .mdd/docs/architecture-tracking.md; update the relevant .mdd/architecture/*.yml; for a decision, APPEND a new entry and mark the prior one superseded (supersededBy) rather than rewriting it; keep components.yml in sync with the component diagrams; the structured change is captured in git (interim) and, in a follow-up cycle, by a structured mdd arch diff/status verb.")
' Objective-side sequence for tracking an architectural change (cycle 0028).
title Tracking an architectural change (objective)

actor "Agent" as Agent
participant ".mdd/docs/architecture-tracking.md" as Doc
participant ".mdd/architecture/*.yml" as Spec
participant "git" as Git

Agent -> Doc : read the tracking workflow
Agent -> Spec : update components / constraints
alt a decision changes
  Agent -> Spec : append new Decision; mark prior superseded
end
Agent -> Git : commit (structured diff is the interim history)
note right of Git: a structured `mdd arch diff` / `status` verb is a follow-up
@enduml
